  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>red onions  </strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-red-onion-flatbreads-rocket-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a lid, with a large drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced red onion</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and reduce the heat to low </p>\n<p>Cover and cook for 6-7 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-red-onion-flatbreads-rocket-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>flaked almonds</strong> to a baking tray and put them in the oven for 3 min or until they've darkened slightly in colour (toasted)  </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-red-onion-flatbreads-rocket-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Crumble</span> the <strong>goats' cheese</strong> and set aside</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-red-onion-flatbreads-rocket-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> – this is your <strong>balsamic dressing</strong></p>\n<p>Slice the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half and set aside  </p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-red-onion-flatbreads-rocket-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>onion marmalade</strong> to the <strong>red onion</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p>\n<p>Remove the pan from the heat  </p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-red-onion-flatbreads-rocket-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>naan breads</strong> to a baking tray</p>\n<p>Spread the <strong>onion mixture</strong> over the <strong>naan breads</strong> and top with the <strong>crumbled goats' cheese</strong> and <strong>black olives</strong></p>\n<p>Put the <strong>naan breads</strong> in the oven for 15 min or until the goats' cheese is starting  to crisp and brown – these are your <strong>Goats' Cheese &amp; Red Onion Flatbreads</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-red-onion-flatbreads-rocket-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash, then pat the <strong>rocket</strong> dry</p>\n<p>Toss the <strong>rocket salad</strong>, <strong>sliced cherry tomatoes</strong> and <strong>toasted almonds</strong> with the <strong>balsamic dressing</strong> </p>\n<p>Tip: don't dress the salad until serving or it will go soggy </p>\n<p>Serve the <strong>salad</strong> alongside the <strong>Goats' Cheese &amp; Red Onion Flatbreads </strong>and enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
